HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1008
By Keisling
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Paula Boone upon her
selection as a 2026 participant in the
THCA/TNCAL Future Leaders Program.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to recognize those
outstanding Tennesseans whose professional achievements reflect dedication, leadership, and
a commitment to excellence; and
WHEREAS, Paula Boone of Signature HealthCARE of Putnam County has been
selected as a 2026 participant in the Tennessee Health Care Association/Tennessee Center for
Assisted Living (THCA/TNCAL) Future Leaders Program; and
WHEREAS, this prestigious program is designed to identify, develop, and prepare the
next generation of long-term care leaders through education on the legislative process,
reimbursement and regulatory issues, leadership development, and association governance;
and
WHEREAS, Ms. Boone's selection for participation in this program reflects her
dedication to the long-term care industry and her commitment to continued professional growth
as a leader; and
WHEREAS, through her service with Signature HealthCARE of Putnam County, Paula
Boone contributes meaningfully to the delivery of quality care and to the advancement of long-
term care in Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Boone's achievement is a source of pride to her colleagues and
community and exemplifies the high standards of professionalism and leadership that
strengthen our State; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
HJR1008
013497
- 1 -

CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Paula Boone upon her selection as a 2026
participant in the THCA/TNCAL Future Leaders Program and extend to her our best wishes for
every continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
